File: Lions' Malcolm Marx makes a break during the Super Rugby match between New Zealand's Waikato Chiefs and South Africa's Golden Lions in Hamilton on April 19, 2019. JOHANNESBURG - Springbok hooker Malcolm Marx has opted to permanently leave the Lions. The Lions could not retain Marx's services after the 25-year-old terminated his contract which was set to begin in July. READ: Black outshines Barrett to give Hurricanes the blues The contract was terminated during the 21-day 'transfer window' part of SA Rugby's salary-cut negotiations brought on by COVID-19. Marx has signed for the Kubota Spears in Japan, coached by Frans Ludeke.